Phase 1 
March 19 , 2026 
Home Lab Journal
Setting up the Ubuntu virtual machine turned out to be one of the most frustrating 
but educational experiences of this project so far. The first major issue was an architecture 
mismatch — I kept downloading the amd64 version of Ubuntu when my UTM environment was running 
ARM64 (aarch64), which caused QEMU to reject the ISO entirely and throw errors on boot. 
After several failed attempts I finally found the correct noble-desktop-arm64.iso and got the 
installer to launch.

The second wave of problems came from storage. The virtual drive was initially too small at around
6-7GB, which caused the Ubuntu installation to fail mid-process. On top of that my Mac itself was 
running low on available storage, which meant I had to clean out old ISO files and free up space 
before I could even resize the VM drive. After bumping the VirtIO drive to 64GB and clearing out 
unnecessary files, the installation finally completed successfully and Ubuntu 24.04 booted cleanly
for the first time.
